#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Tails is being distributed free of charge because we strongly believe that "
"[[free software is more secure by design|doc/about/trust#free_software]]. "
"But also because we think that **nobody should have to pay to be safe while "
"using computers**. Unfortunately, Tails cannot stay alive without money as "
"developing Tails and maintaining our infrastructure has a cost."
msgstr ""
"Tails es distribueix gratuïtament perquè creiem fermament que el "
"[[Programari Lliure és més segur per disseny|doc/about/"
"trust#free_software]]. Però també perquè pensem que **ningú hauria de pagar "
"per mantenir-se fora de perill mentre utilitza ordinadors**. Malauradament, "
"Tails no pot mantenir-se viu sense diners, ja que desenvolupar Tails i "
"mantenir la nostra infraestructura té un cost."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We rely solely on donations from individuals and supporting organizations to "
"keep Tails updated and getting always better.  **That's why we need your "
"help!**"
msgstr ""
"Depenem únicament de les donacions de persones i organitzacions de suport "
"per mantenir Tails actualitzat i millorar sempre. **Per això necessitem la "
"vostra ajuda!**"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If you find Tails useful, please consider [[donating money|donate]] or "
"[[contributing some of your time and skills|contribute]] to the project.  "
"Donations to Tails are tax-deductible both in the US and in Europe."
msgstr ""
"Si trobeu útil Tails, considereu [[fer una donació econòmica|donate]] o "
"[[aportar part del vostre temps i habilitats|contribute]] al projecte. Les "
"donacions a Tails són deduïbles d'impostos tant als EUA com a Europa."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In October 2014, Tails was being used by more than 11 500 people daily. The "
"profile of Tor and Tails users is very diverse. This diversity increases the "
"anonymity provided by those tools for everyone by making it harder to target "
"and to identify a specific type of user. From the various contacts that we "
"have with organizations working on the ground, we know that Tails has been "
"used by:"
msgstr ""
"L'octubre de 2014, Tails estava sent utilitzat per més d'11 500 persones "
"diàriament. El perfil dels usuaris de Tor i Tails és molt divers. Aquesta "
"diversitat augmenta l'anonimat que proporcionen aquestes eines per a tothom, "
"ja que dificulta l'orientació i la identificació d'un tipus específic "
"d'usuari. Pels diferents contactes que tenim amb organitzacions que "
"treballen sobre el terreny, sabem que Tails ha estat utilitzat per:"

